    "body": "Related:\r\n\r\nI think lighthouse reads the full file, including any whitespace: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/ad4e5adabc7b68a9e06ffc17a2df20575100e283/common/validator_dir/src/validator_dir.rs#L235\r\n\r\nWhile teku only reads the first line: https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/4239bddd68c45aa0bcce6d7a6f7c3392c3f465b9/teku/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/teku/cli/deposit/KeystorePasswordOptions.java#L35\r\n\r\ncc @paulhauner we should standardize how passwords are read and written, so that a user does not get surprised when their password with whitespace from teku is invalid in lighthouse, or similar things the other way around (teku reading passwords as utf-8, while we could support raw bytes). There's already someone in the lighthouse discord who has this problem I think.\r\n",
