    "created_at": "2020-08-31T01:46:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-08-31T01:46:16Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So with the changes to EIP2335 linked above, the password is explicitly a string of unicode characters.  It doesn't specify what unicode encoding is used when storing on disk which still leaves room for incompatibility between clients - Teku will continue to use UTF-8.\n\nEIP2335 now requires all control characters to be stripped, so line endings at the end of the file should now be stripped by all clients (as would line endings in the middle of the file).  Teku will change to read the entire file for simplicity and the normalisation process will strip any trailing line endings.\n\nRaised https://github.com/PegaSysEng/signers/pull/59 to implement these changes and will then need to pull that into Teku.",
